{"id":"11143","name":"Generate Shortcuts Run Links List","tagline":"Generate an unordered list of titled markdown links to run each shortcut in a specified folder.","icon":"ios15 c4292093695 g61440","latest":"31939","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3>Requirements</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/text-case/id1492174677\">Text Case for iOS</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/data-jar/id1453273600\">Data Jar for iOS</a> (More or less optional.)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This shortcut generates an unordered markdown list (-) of markdown-formatted links to run one’s shortcuts using <code>shortcuts://x-callback-url/run-shortcut?name=</code>, optionally stores the titled links in a Data Jar List, and copies the result to the clipboard. At least for the moment, it is limited to running <em>on</em> a remote Mac using a <code>Run Script Over SSH</code> action <em>from</em> a local iOS-running device.</p>\n<p>Theoretically, it could be accomplished using the native <a href=\"https://www.matthewcassinelli.com/actions/url-encode/\">URL Encode action</a> instead of <a href=\"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/text-case/id1492174677\">Text Case for iOS</a>, but - after several hours’ worth of configuring and re-configuring, I was unable to get the former to produce reliable results. </p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/extratone/i/blob/main/shortcuts/Generate%20Shortcuts%20Run%20Links%20List.xml\">Source (XML)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/extratone/i/blob/main/shortcuts/Generate%20Shortcuts%20Run%20Links%20List.json\">Source (JSON)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/extratone/i/blob/main/shortcuts/Generate%20Shortcuts%20Run%20Links%20List.html\">Web Review (HTML)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/extratone/i/raw/main/shortcuts/Generate%20Shortcuts%20Run%20Links%20List.shortcut\">File</a></li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h2>Contact</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://davidblue.wtf/db.vcf\">Contact Card</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://t.